    ourTeam.innerHTML = " <h3 {text-align: center; padding-bottom: 10px;}>Directors</h3> <img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/raymond-yap.png' alt='raymond yap'><h4>Raymond Yap</h4> <h5>Founder & CEO</h5> <p>Raymond spent 30 years in business, primarily heading up the European operations for Wong’s International Ltd., a major electronics manufacturing group listed in Hong Kong. He also worked with Mondex, part of the Mastercard suite of smart card companies.</p><p>In 1991 Raymond opted for early retirement, emigrating to Vancouver to enjoy life and prioritise spending more time with his family. In 2003, he was diagnosed with melanoma, an aggressive form of skin cancer, and subsequently underwent life-saving surgery. This proved to be a cathartic experience for him, generating concern for his family particularly his young grandchildren with a realization that the best way to safeguard their future was to protect the environment. Eager to create lasting change, Raymond came out of retirement and applied his business acumen and experience to advocating environmental protection. To this end he set up HeroesToo Foundation Ltd., an eco-education charity and SolutionsToo Ltd., an environmental social enterprise. He is an affiliate member of the Hong Kong Business Environment Council.</p> <p>E-mail: <a style= 'color: white;' href='mailto:raymond@heroestoo.com'> raymond@heroestoo.com</a></p> <p {text-decoration: none}>Phone: (852) 6403-0208</p><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/ka-lun-to.png' alt='Ka-Lun To'><h4>Ka-Lun To</h4><h5>Director</h5><p>Ka-Lun, better known as KL, is a District Councillor in Hong Kong for Yuen Long. He is a Director with HeroesToo since its inception and supports its mission by action. His involvement with HeroesToo and its care for mankind and the ecosystem helps keep his balance of work he does in the digital world. An engineer and IT specialist with diversified experience working with corporates and NGOs’, KL has been deeply involved with promoting IT Security practices in Hong Kong.</p><p>Ever since taking office as a Yuen Long District Councillor, he ensured environmental issues were put on the Council agenda by taking leads in various roles within. As well as publicising and promoting awareness to the local community. Recently, he lobbied the Council for total abolishment of plastic bottle usage and to stop financing the same for all project applications. Renown in his district for being Green, he is often sighted riding his bicycle to council meetings!</p><p>E-mail: <a style= 'color: white;' href='mailto:kalunto@fvdco.hk'>kalunto@fvdco.hk</a></p><p {text-decoration: none}>Phone: (852) 69238336</p><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/christopher-curry.png' alt='christopher-curry'><p><h4>Christopher Curry</h4><h5>Co-Founder</h5><p>Chris co-founded HeroesToo Ltd. as well as Acorn Computers. His early career was in electronics helping Sinclair Electronics launch its first electronic calculator, the Executive, one of the first of its kind in the market. He set up Acorn Computers, whose first product was the Acorn Microcomputer. He became a millionaire as a result of Acorn’s success with the BBC Micro computer, backed by the BBC and used in schools across the UK. He continues to work in technology innovation and his current company, General Information Services, is one of the leading companies in background screening, smart cards and in 2012, he announced his latest project, Care with Canary, developing innovative systems for helping the elderly at home.</p><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/eleanor-sackett.png' alt='Eleanor Sackett'><h4>Eleanor Sackett</h4><h5>Director</h5><p>Eleanor believes lowering our carbon footprint is dependent on a better understanding of the urgency of today’s environmental issues, spreading the knowledge and motivating the community, especially our youth, to get involved and play a bigger role in environmental sustainability. She commends the EcoPledge Education Program as a means of providing this to our younger generation, inspiring ownership and action and to enhance the collaborative process.</p><p>Brought up in Hong Kong, she has a comprehensive understanding of local culture and issues towards change and the environment. She has worked for multinational corporations globally and brings her marketing and management experience to align HeroesToo goals with the community at large to help create the momentum for essential environmental impact. Her altruism is reflected in the voluntary work she undertakes for a number of non-profit organisations. When not engaged in pro-bono work, she is an events management consultant and plays squash recreationally.</p><br><hr style='opacity: .3'}><h3 {text-align: center;}>Advisory Board Members</h3><hr style='opacity: .1; width: 50%;'}><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/mark-harper.png' alt='Mark Harper'><h4>Mark Harper</h4><p>Mark is a highly skilled programme manager & communicator with ten years experience managing & implementing corporate/NGO partnerships in the Asia, Latin America, North America & European markets. He has strong experience especially in the areas of CSR/sustainability reporting and community investment.</p><p>He works in the sustainability division of a large multinational conglomerate and is on the board of the Business Environment Council.  Mark was the Policy Research & ESG Advisory Manager providing consultancy services on ESG management and reporting. Prior to that, as Manager of China Water Risk, his role involved writing water-related thought leadership pieces and conducting sector-specific research into water risk for finance companies.</p><p>Throughout his career, Mark has been involved in corporate sustainability, working with corporations on how to embed sustainability into the DNA of how they do business. In his previous roles, he has been involved in building & managing effective strategic partnership programmes across both the corporate & public sector encompassing all stages of programme development & management, from writing the proposal, budget preparation, to logistical planning, roll out & reporting.</p><p>Mark has a strong background in ESG Reporting, employee engagement & CSR education. Previously he was part of the leadership team responsible for the management and delivery of the HSBC Climate Partnership. He was responsible for the management & delivery of the employee & stakeholder engagement aspects of an award-winning sustainability leadership programme. This engagement programme ran in partnership with HSBC, WWF, Climate Group, the Smithsonian Tropical Research Initiative, supported world-class scientific research and an innovative employee/local stakeholder learning programme.</p><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/wanda-huang.png' alt='Wanda Huang'><h4>Wanda Huang</h4> <p>Wanda is an experienced educator, permaculture practitioner and conservationist from Canada. Her work has ranged from promoting experiential learning and environmental programmes in Hong Kong to working on permaculture projects in eco-communities and organic farms in Asia. Wanda is a qualified secondary school teacher with 17 years of teaching and curriculum development experience. She has traveled to over 100 countries and has worked within the tertiary and secondary education sectors and as a curriculum development officer for the Education Bureau (EDB) of Hong Kong.</p><p>A native-English speaker, Wanda is also fluent in Cantonese and Mandarin. She holds Masters Degrees in Psychology, Education, and Linguistics (TESOL) from Canada, Hong Kong, and the UK respectively. She has worked tirelessly with experiential learning providers, social enterprises and NGOs on promoting outdoor educational and sustainability projects across schools in Hong Kong, China, Canada and New Zealand.</p><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/hamilton-le.png' alt='Hamilton Le'><p><h4>Hamilton Le</h4><p>Hamilton is a product manager fascinated with bringing solutions to market, full stack technologies, UI/UX, bootstrapping fun ideas, diving head first into data and giving talks on leadership. He is passionate about educational initiatives and was previously involved with AIESEC, spearheading educational programs in the Hong Kong, US, and the Middle East.</p><p>Hamilton is a Chicago native currently dividing his time between in Shanghai & Hong Kong and in his spare time, you can find him on his cello or guitar.</p><br><br><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535034638/heroes-too/merrin-oearse.png' alt='Merrin Pearse'><h4>Dr. Merrin Pearse</h4> Merrin has been involved in multiple global projects, including the quality assurance of United Nations border missions, auditing of engineering projects, training and facilitation in the use of new technology and processes. His background, training and experience in geodesy and engineering in locations as diverse as Antarctica and East Africa enables him to provide a practical approach to achieving long-term goals and vision.<p></p>He holds a Doctor of Philosophy in Geodesy & Geomatic Engineering from the University of New South Wales and a Bachelor of Surveying from the University of Otago.<p></p>His most recent position was acting Chief Executive Officer with Friends of the Earth (HK) involved as a project manager in communication and a senior environmental officer on a corporate sector low carbon initiative. Elsewhere he has delivered experiential learning programmes on sustainability, worked for the Earth Champions and Ecovision Asia. Merrin is active in community groups, chairman of the Living Islands Movement, co-organiser of Hong Kong Green Drinks and an external advisor to AIESEC Hong Kong Baptist University.</p><hr style='opacity: .3'}><h3 {text-align: center;}>Our Interns</h3><h5 style='text-align: center; padding-bottom: 60px'>HeroesToo welcomes interns to gain meaningful work experience and refine their skill sets.</h5><img src='https://res.cloudinary.com/dofuzeof4/image/upload/v1535035464/heroes-too/interns.png' alt='Heroes Too Interns' style='max-width: 300px; width: auto;'><p>We are very fortunate in having an awesome team of multinational, talented and eco friendly interns sharing their skills and vivacity with us this summer to reach our goals for a greener world.</p><p>Our 2018 Heroes (Standing L to R): Himeshika Samaradivakara (English, City University Hong Kong), Asah Walen (Political Science, St. Michael’s College VA, USA), Eleanor Sackett (Director, HeroesToo), Will Harend (Bali, Indonesia. Graduate B.Com Curtin University, Singapore), Dane Knotts (Philosophy & Political Science, UC Davis CA, USA),  Michelle Luu (International Relations & Communications, UC Davis CA, USA).(Seated L to R): Tabitha Boyton (Cheltenham Ladies’ College, England), Monique Hui, (BA Business Administration, Hang Seng Management College, Hong Kong), Claudia Acuna (Architecture, Skyline College, San Bruno CA, USA), Samantha Yuen (Environmental Management & Technology, Hong Kong University of Science and Technology)</p><p>Absent from photo: Simon Semenoff (Russia, MA Chinese Business, Hong Kong Polytechnic University) and Toby Sumagaysay (Tourism and Hospitality, Royal Brisbane Institute of Technology, Hong Kong).</p>"
